e6 10. O-O Bd6 11. Bxd6 Qxd6
{ The position is still very dry, but at least one set of Bishops chose to do different things. Black's plan if White does nothing is to castle and double on the c-file, which would leave him with a great position. White can  (and probably should)  try to abuse the weakened c5 square, but I think Black is still okay. }
12. Qb3 Rc7 { No Nb5. a7-a6 really did turn out to be useful ! } 13. Na4 O-O
